k\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 25, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yft1665702989809.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yft1665702989809.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yft1665702989809.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yft1665702989809\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">psdef.txt</span> file is a configuration file for PostScript printing on Unix platforms.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yft1665702989809__section_w5606ab1b5b1_w5607ab1b5_w5608ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d464590e53\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yft1665702989809__p_d176402e1_d176403e1_d176404e1\">You can edit the <span class=\"ph filepath\">psdef.txt</span> to override default font mappings or add paper sizes. The file contains other sections as well, but it is recommended that you not modify these.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yft1665702989809__p_d176405e1_d176406e1_d176407e1\">A <code class=\"ph codeph\">#</code> character at the beginning of any line in this file denotes a comment.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yft1665702989809__section_w5609ab1b5b3_w5610ab1b5_w5611ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d464590e71\">File Sections</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yft1665702989809__p_d176411e1_d176412e1_d176413e1\">The file is divided into the following sections:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yft1665702989809__li_d53804e1_d53805e1_d53806e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"grv1665702989881.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/grv1665702989881.html\" title=\"The [FONTS] section defines logical fonts that override those used by default, when printing to PostScript.\">[FONTS]</a>—font mappings.\n               For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"giv1665702989665.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/giv1665702989665.html\" title=\"Font rendering for PostScript depends on the font files on your machine. Only Adobe PostScript Type 1 fonts are supported for PostScript printing.\">Font Support for PostScript Output</a>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yft1665702989809__li_d53807e1_d53808e1_d53809e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jxv1665702990013.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jxv1665702990013.html\" title=\"The [background] and [foreground] sections of psddef.txt determine how PostScript color definitions are mapped to PostScript colors.\">[background] and [foreground]</a>—color mappings\n               for printing.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yft1665702989809__li_d53810e1_d53811e1_d53812e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tay1665702990082.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tay1665702990082.html\" title=\"The [PAPERS] section specifies default paper sizes available for printing to PostScript.\">[PAPERS]</a>—paper size\n               definitions.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yft1665702989809__li_d53813e1_d53814e1_d53815e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mid1665702990151.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mid1665702990151.html\" title=\"The [GENERAL] section contains configuration settings for compression and encoding of binary data, such as images.\">[GENERAL]</a>—compression and\n               encoding parameters</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534071\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534071\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "psdef.txt Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 25, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The psdef.txt file is a configuration file for PostScript printing on Unix platforms. Description You can edit the psdef.txt to override default font mappings or add paper sizes. The file contains other sections as well, but it is recommended that you not modify these. A # character at the beginning of any line in this file denotes a comment. File Sections The file is divided into the following sections: [FONTS] —font mappings. For more information, see Font Support for PostScript Output . [background] and [foreground] —color mappings for printing. [PAPERS] —paper size definitions. [GENERAL] —compression and encoding parameters Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}